This paper is primarily focused on robotic grasping, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of reinforcement learning (RL) to learn grasping policies falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision (cs.CV) to perceive the environment and the use of HER to improve learning, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
